(the technique) Sounds familiar, but we don't discuss Mohs much here.
What was the size of the lesion?  Steph might be able to say if shave biopsy
would have been better or RT.

If you're implying that you're going to a surgeon and it was not cancer to begin
with, then why go to that doctor?  Things work differently in each country. In
our country, (Canada), we usually see a GP (primary care physician) who are
usually pretty good at identifying skin lesions/lumps that need referral.
Isn't there one in your area?
